result.name: Bauhinia Kitchen

reviews.text:
This is one of the best Chinese restaurants I have had in Hong Kong.  
One of the famous dishes is the ‘Beggar duck’ (叫化鴨) is excellent.  Treated sticky rice with other ingredients are put inside the duck which is then wrapped up with mud and roasted in the oven.  One should eat the duck meat with other ingredients together for the best taste; just like many people like to have red wine goes with cheese.  This dish should better be ordered in advance and the portion is a bit large which is good for a party of 6 or more.
It has a number of other outstanding and traditional dishes which are difficult to be found in other large restaurants.

We used to visit the old Bauhinia on Waterloo Road. We were so happy to enjoy the their dishes after 5~6 years. And the super nice thing was that we met the lady boss. She has not changed much. The atmosphere is quite nice. We enjoyed the service and the meal. We definitely will return for the old style Cantonese cooking, which is a rarity these days.

Service is excellent. They are so attentive to my surprise and even telling us how to reheat the pudding at home

I liked the 蝦子魚肚 the most，魚腸 is way too fishy
Not too noisy, we went there for our ex classmate reunion
Good at food and service

result.name: 紫荊閣

reviews.text: 價錢貴咗少少🤭
主打懷舊菜有特色。叫化雞同八寶鴨材料多入味，但係肉質太腍冇頭over咗，有啲過份吹捧。杉班嫩滑。螺頭豬湯入味。蓮蓉焗布甸唔係太甜唔錯。整體可以。
飲茶可以，原因在同區中較安靜，蝦餃算有水準，碗裝湯麵也好 ; 但晚飯不推薦，懷舊菜等等不甚了了。
點心様樣得，其他食品水凖之上…
地方環境不錯，坐位舒適，食物質素好，服務生態度亦算好。上菜次序方面有改善空間。
